  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Roll out the puff pastry to a thickness of 1/8 inch.",
    "Transfer the pastry to a 9-inch pie dish.",
    "In a bowl, mix together the smoked paprika, onion powder, garlic powder, cheddar cheese, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the beaten egg to the bowl and mix until a dough forms.",
    "Pour the dough into the pie crust.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the pastry is golden brown.",
    "Let cool for 10 minutes before serving."
